    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A polysemous term used for the community centre of each tlaxilacalli (neighbourhood) in Mexico-Tenochtitlan during the postclassic period. It was used for events related to the population's identity.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Un término polisémico utilizado para designar al centro comunitario de cada tlaxilacalli (barrio) de México-Tenochtitlán durante el período posclásico. Se utilizaba para eventos relacionados con la identidad de la población.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tlahtolli tlen motequihuia para momanextiz tlahtlacopan tlen ce altepetzin tlen cehcen tlaxilacalli tlen Mexco-Tenochtitlan ipan cahuitl posclasico. Motequihuiyaya para tlaixpiyalli tlen monehpanoa ica inintlaneltoquil tlen altepetzitzin.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
